bug.summary: Link to youtube video on YOLOv5 Detection model README page is broken
bug.description:
<denchmark-h:h4>Version</denchmark-h>
Not Applicable <denchmark-h:h4>Description</denchmark-h>

Opening that URL in a browser gives a Youtube error page with "Video unavailable". <denchmark-h:h4>Configuration</denchmark-h>
Not Applicable <denchmark-h:h4>Steps to reproduce</denchmark-h>
Click on the link in the sentence "... this youtube video will be used." in the README

It should link to <denchmark-link:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aUdKzb4LGJI>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aUdKzb4LGJI</denchmark-link> rather than <denchmark-link:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aUdKzb4LGJ>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aUdKzb4LGJ</denchmark-link> .
